Press Release
 


For Immediate Release:
Eeonyx signs exclusive LOI with BeBop Sensors
Spinout from Keith McMillen Instruments to develop sensors with Eeonyx
April 23, 2014
Pinole CA
Eeonyx Corp signed a Letter of Intent to make BeBop Sensors, Inc. of Berkeley, CA its exclusive licensee for sensor fabrics.
BeBop was recently launched by Keith McMillen Instruments (KMI), maker of the world’s most responsive computer music controllers.  KMI has worked with Eeonyx over the last 5 years advancing the state of the art in smart fabric sensors.
Eeonyx is the premier provider of conductive fabrics used as microwave and RF absorbers, and flexible heaters. Eeonyx conductive fabrics create touchscreen capable gloves.
KMI has over a million discrete sensors made from Eeonyx fabric in active use. Numerous requests from outside the music industry prompted KMI to create BeBop Sensors to provide solutions for robotic, sports, medical, Internet of Things and other applications.
BeBop CEO Keith McMillen says, “Creating sensors that are responsive and robust has been the focus of KMI’s work with Eeonyx.  I am pleased to announce the plan to formalize and advance our relationship through BeBop Sensors”.
Jimmy Holliman, CEO of Eeonyx says, “We are very excited to extend our relationship with Keith McMillen and aggressively pursue new market applications and opportunities for our sensors”.
When completed, the agreement will make BeBop Sensors the WW provider of sensors designed with Eeonyx smart fabric. The companies will work together to improve and refine materials and applications to take advantage of the growing opportunity of wearable, flexible, robust, responsive and affordable sensors for demanding applications.
Products and press from KMI can be seen at:
http://files.keithmcmillen.com/company_press/KMI_Press_Highlights_web.pdf
http://www.eeonyx.com
 
 
 

Contact info@bebopsensors.com


 
 
 




















